**I'll build a modern, production-ready collaborative notes app for teams.**

### Core Features
- **Auth**: Email/password signup/login (secure, session-based)
- **Teams**: Create teams, invite/join members (role-based: admin/member)
- **Notes**: Shared team notes with title + rich Markdown content, authorship, timestamps
- **Permissions**: Only team members can view/edit notes for that team
- **UI**: Clean dashboard, team switcher, note list + editor, dark mode ready
- **Stack** (easy to run locally, zero external paid services):
  - Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript
  - Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui-inspired components
  - Prisma + SQLite (file-based — swap to Postgres later with 1 line)
  - NextAuth.js (credentials)
  - bcrypt for passwords
  - react-markdown + simple textarea editor (easy to upgrade to TipTap/Plate later)

This is fully self-contained. You can run it with `npm install && npx prisma db push && npm run dev`.

